            <TITLE>
               <P>The skilled worker survey</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>2017/3723</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="73110000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>The work on quality in learning a trade shall contribute to pupils and apprentices receiving relevant training in a good learning environment and that they complete their training. The quality development includes setting targets, implementing relevant measures to achieve the targets and assessing whether the targets have been achieved.</P>
               <P>The Norwegian Directorate for Education and Training shall provide information about the quality of learning a trade. The obtained information from the survey shall form the basis for the national policy development. The Directorate´s work on quality in learning a trade is further discussed in the documented Quality in Learning a Trade. Description of the quality assessment system for schools and apprentice companies (the Norwegian Directorate of Education and Training).</P>
               <P>As a part of obtaining information and a knowledge basis in the quality development work, the Norwegian Directorate of Education and Training is responsible for several user surveys, such as:</P>
               <P>— the Pupil Survey,</P>
               <P>— the Apprentice Survey, and,</P>
               <P>— the Apprentice Company Survey.</P>
               <P>These three surveys provide, amongst other things, information on pupils and apprentices´ training environments at school and in companies.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <VAL_TOTAL CURRENCY="NOK">2000000.00</VAL_TOTAL>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="NO"/>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>The work on quality in learning a trade shall contribute to pupils and apprentices receiving relevant training in a good learning environment and that they complete their training. The quality development includes setting targets, implementing relevant measures to achieve the targets and assessing whether the targets have been achieved.</P>
                  <P>The Norwegian Directorate for Education and Training shall provide information about the quality of learning a trade. The obtained information from the survey shall form the basis for the national policy development. The Directorate´s work on quality in learning a trade is further discussed in the documented Quality in Learning a Trade. Description of the quality assessment system for schools and apprentice companies (the Norwegian Directorate of Education and Training).</P>
                  <P>As a part of obtaining information and a knowledge basis in the quality development work, the Norwegian Directorate of Education and Training is responsible for several user surveys, such as the Pupil Survey, the Apprentice Survey and the Apprentice Company Survey. These three surveys provide, amongst other things, information on pupils and apprentices´ training environments at school and in companies.</P>
                  <P>A general aim of learning a trade is that it shall be of high quality and the relevance of the training for working life is an important criterion when assessing quality. There are, however, no indicators that give information on the relevance of learning a trade for working life and this is a challenge as regards assessing the quality of learning a trade.</P>
                  <P>The parliamentary bill St. 20 'På rett vei' points out that there is a need for knowledge in order to assess whether there is a good connection between the content of the educational courses and the labor market´s demand for competence.</P>
                  <P>A survey shall be established aimed at skilled workers (the Skilled Worker Survey) as a part of obtaining more knowledge on the relevance of learning a trade. The survey will be a part of a large knowledge basis that will form the basis for an assessment of the relevance of learning a trade and the parties in working life are important dialogue parties in the work.</P>
                  <P>The target groups for the result of the survey are the Ministry of Education and Research, the Norwegian Directorate for Education and Training, the Co-operation council for vocational training (SRY), the professional councils and counties.</P>
                  <P>A brief description of the assignment:</P>
                  <P>— the assignment includes the development and implementation of a survey directed towards skilled workers,</P>
                  <P>— the assignment can be viewed as a piloting project where the objective is to evaluate whether or not the survey shall be implemented on a regular basis after the assignment is concluded.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
